commentary: Mohammad Nabi to Simi Singh, OUT length, and he plays from the crease, and he's been given leg-before! Good, consistent bowling from Nabi pays off, just pitching outside off and turning back in. Struck him in line, as he was stretching forward to meet it. Looks like it may have gone on to clip middle and leg. Breaks what was turning into a useful little resistance, as Stirling continues to lose partners!
shortText: Mohammad Nabi to Simi Singh, OUT
text: length, and he plays from the crease, and he's been given leg-before! Good, consistent bowling from Nabi pays off, just pitching outside off and turning back in. Struck him in line, as he was stretching forward to meet it. Looks like it may have gone on to clip middle and leg. Breaks what was turning into a useful little resistance, as Stirling continues to lose partners!

commentary: McCarthy to Hazratullah Zazai, OUT fuller ball, and he has swung this around, and been taken! He challenges long on, where the fielder stationed is big man Kevin O'Brien, and this is an excellent catch. The ball was sailing over his head, but he caught it, made sure he kept his feet inside the field while taking the catch. Stepped out momentarily for balance, but had already tossed the ball up, and then stepped back in nonchalantly to complete the catch. Big wicket for Ireland, especially in how well timed it is

commentary: Simi Singh to Hashmatullah Shahidi, OUT beauty of a ball! This is pitched up, just outside off stump, and invites a tentative poke from Shahidi, and just takes a feather-edge on its way through to Poynter, who holds on. The Irish team celebrates, as this breaks what was looking like a useful association after two quick wickets

commentary: Dockrell to Gulbadin Naib, OUT there won't be a fifty for Naib! Tossed up, and pitched on leg stump, and Naib was looking to just work it towards midwicket. Got the leading edge and floated back towards Dockrell, who clings on gleefully. An effective knock from Naib comes to an end, with the final acceleration probably doing enough to seal this deal for Afghanistan

commentary: Dockrell to Najibullah Zadran, SIX runs full, and he tonks this over midwicket. Victory for Afghanistan, and with an emphatic slog sweep by the birthday boy!
